criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age 18 to 80 years;

          -  Subject has solitary symptomatic intracranial atherosclerosis that the degree of the
             artery stenosis is between 70% and 99% diagnosed by angiography；

          -  The target artery locates in Vertebral Artery(VA), Internal Carotid Artery(ICA),
             Middle Cerebral Artery(MCA) or Basilar Artery(BA);

          -  Subject has at least two atherosclerosis risk factors including diabetes, history or
             present hypertension, hyperlipidemia, smoking, age>45；

          -  Modified Rankin Scale(mRS) score≤2 before enrollment;

          -  Subject or legal representative is able to understand the purpose of study, agrees to
             to provide follow-up data and has provided written informed consent;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of severe ischemic stroke within 2 weeks；

          -  History of intracranial hemorrhage(including intraparenchymal hemorrhage, massive
             subarachnoid hemorrhage, subdural hemorrhage and epidural hemorrhage) within 3 months;

          -  Hypertension uncontrolled by medicine(Systolic pressure≥180 mmHg or diastolic
             pressure≥110mmHg continuously);

          -  Associated intracranial arteriovenous malformation, aneurysms or tumors;

          -  The length of the target vessel>10mm and acute angle>90°;

          -  History of stent intervention within the target vessel;

          -  Allergic to heparin, sirolimus, contrast agents, aspirin, clopidogrel, anesthetics；

          -  History of gastrointestinal hemorrhage within 6 months before providing informed
             consent or unable to receive antiplatelet therapy；

          -  Platelet(PLT)<90*10^9/L;

          -  Creatinine>250umol/L;

          -  International Normalized Ratio(INR)>1.5;

          -  Expected life <12 months;

          -  Female subjects who are pregnant, having a pregnancy plan, or lactating within the
             study period;

          -  Unable to cooperate with or tolerate the interventional surgery;

          -  Subjects who have participated in other clinical investigations or haven't reach the
             primary end point;

          -  Intracranial artery stenosis caused by arterial dissection, arteritis, and thrombosis;

          -  Unsuitable tortuous artery for delivery, deployment and retrieval of the device;

          -  The degree of stenosis within the non-responsibility vessels>70%;

          -  Other circumstances judged by researchers that are not suitable for enrollment;
